modules.name: Dissect.Class
modules.comments:
Provides the `Dissect` type class based on the "Clowns to the Left of me,
Jokers to the Right (Pearl): Dissecting Data Structures" paper by Conor
McBride.

declarations.comments:
The result of a dissection step over some data structure `p`, which can
either be a `yield`, indicating that additional steps would have to be
performed; or a `return`, indicating that the dissection has finished.
declarations.title: Result

children.comments: Initializes a dissection given the base structure `p j`.
children.title: init

children.comments:
Advances a dissection by filling in the intermediary structure `q c j`
with some value `c`.
children.title: next

declarations.comments:
The type class for dissectible data structures, which generalizes the
traversal of some `Functor p` given an intermediary `Bifunctor q`.
declarations.title: Dissect

declarations.comments: A tail-recursive `map` operation, implemented in terms of `Dissect`.
declarations.title: map

declarations.comments:
A tail-recursive `traverse` operation, implemented in terms of `Dissect`.

Derived from: https://blog.functorial.com/posts/2017-06-18-Stack-Safe-Traversals-via-Dissection.html
declarations.title: traverse

declarations.comments: A tail-recursive `sequence` operation, implemented in terms of `Dissect`.
declarations.title: sequence

modules.name: Dissect.Generic
modules.comments:
Polynomial functors and bifunctors for algebraically defining data types
with free `Dissect` instances as described in "Algebra of Programming" by
Bird and de Moor; as well as the functional dissections paper.

declarations.comments: The constant functor, which maps all `b` to some constant `a`.
declarations.title: Const

declarations.comments: The identity functor, which maps all `a` back into `a`.
declarations.title: Id

declarations.comments: The product of polynomial functors.
declarations.title: Product

declarations.comments: The sum of polynomial functors.
declarations.title: Sum

modules.name: Dissect.Record
modules.comments:
Record-based product types, `RecordF` and `RecordB` which form a `Dissect`
instance. Useful for defining data types algebraically while also having
decent runtime performance and convenient pattern matching syntax.

declarations.comments: A record-based product type of functors applied to `a`.
declarations.title: RecordF

declarations.comments: The internal representation for `RecordF`.
declarations.title: RecordFRep

declarations.comments: A record-based product type of bifunctors applied to `a` and `b`.
declarations.title: RecordB

declarations.comments: A pair of a `Functor` and a `Bifunctor`.
declarations.title: Pair

declarations.comments: Converts a `Record` into a `RecordF`.
declarations.title: From

declarations.comments: Converts a `RecordF` into a `Record`.
declarations.title: To

modules.name: Dissect.Variant
modules.comments:
Row-based sum types, `VariantF` and `VariantB`, which form a `Dissect`
instance. Useful for defining data types algebraically while also having
decent runtime performance and convenient pattern matching syntax.

declarations.comments: A pair of a `Functor` and a `Bifunctor`.
declarations.title: Pair

declarations.comments:
A row-based sum type of functors applied to `a`.

Unlike `VariantF` in the `variant` package, this type is indexed by a row
of `Pair` types, which is also used to index the `VariantB` type.
declarations.title: VariantF

declarations.comments: The internal representation for `VariantF`.
declarations.title: VariantFRep

declarations.comments: Inject into a variant functor given a tag.
declarations.title: injF

declarations.comments: A row-based sum type of bifunctors applied to `a` and `b`.
declarations.title: VariantB

declarations.comments: The internal representation for `VariantB`.
declarations.title: VariantBRep

declarations.comments: Inject into a variant bifunctor given a tag.
declarations.title: injB
